title: CaO$_{2}$(H$_{2}$O)$_{8}$ Structure
comments: This structure was proposed by (Shineman, 1951) to replace the \href{current_web_home_dir/A8B2C_tP11_123_r_h_a-001}{$E6_{2}$ SrO$_{2}$(H$_{2}$O)$_{8}$ structure}.  The unit cell is doubled in the (001) direction, and the oxygens are now molecular.
